        <div id="about" class="sec-label">About</div>
        <div class="body-text">
          I am an Artificial Intelligence Researcher, currently working as an Associate Professor of Computer Science and Engineering at Adamas University, Kolkata[cite: 2]. My academic and research journey spans over two decades across India and Europe, with expertise in artificial intelligence, soft computing, and data-driven optimization algorithms (NSO, PSO, GWO)[cite: 2]. I have spent many years abroad[cite: 2]. I have held several research positions at the Norwegian University of Science and Technology (NTNU), Norway contributing to pioneering projects in cyber-physical systems, Computer Vision & Digital Twin Systems, and industrial AI[cite: 2].<br><br>
          My core interests lie in nature-inspired algorithms, surrogate-assisted optimization, and intelligent manufacturing systems[cite: 2]. I have published extensively in high-impact journals and conferences, and I actively supervise PhD scholars in cutting-edge domains such as prompt engineering and reinforcement learning[cite: 2].<br><br>
          I have also served as a NAAC coordinator and played key academic roles in curriculum development, international collaborations, and quality assurance[cite: 2]. As a recognized reviewer and editorial contributor, I continue to support the scholarly community[cite: 2]. My research has been backed by international grants, and I have led proposals in digital transformation for industries ranging from automotive to food processing[cite: 2]. I am committed to bridging academia and industry through innovation, digital intelligence, and sustainable technology[cite: 2].
